We endeavor to bring added value through innovative and creative solutions to the needs of our clients. Our team-oriented approach has been praised as effectively supporting challenging and time-sensitive transactions. Tavernier Tschanz is regularly described by directories and guides as "punching above its weight" given our client base and the transactions that we handle.
YOU

	are a Swiss qualified lawyer (avocat/Rechtsanwalt) with strong academic credentials;
	work in English and French or in English and German;
	are highly motivated to join and strengthen a leading corporate law team;
	have at least two/three years of experience in corporate finance, M&A and corporate/commercial law in Switzerland (five/six for a senior associate position);
	hold a LLM or had professional experience abroad; and
	are willing to handle matters both autonomously and in a team environment.

WE OFFER

	the opportunity to work on very diverse, high-profile, interesting and challenging transactions and corporate and commercial assignments;
	direct contacts with sophisticated clients, including their CEOs, CFOs and GCs, in diverse industries;
	a motivating team environment within a small team; and
	opportunities for development and promotion, including access to partnership.

If you are interested, please email your complete application to Phidias Ferrari at [email]"}

